<br>
However...the main reason I ever brought up a Sev rotation was to end the competition.  Competition is good, and I'm a very competitive person...but we all know where it can lead (just look at the recent situation with VoF/NB and Sev).  If we were to say no alliances at all then I could see people getting pissed off and alliances racing the rotation guilds.  I do NOT want to see that happen.<br>
<br>
So I really don't see a problem with alliances trying out Sev.  Also Maly, you have to remember that as Karadin has said before...Sev isn't a walk in the park.  He has been upgraded from before and even lvl 60s will be effected by his stun.  I highly doubt every alliance on the Rathe can handle Sev, but I also don't think they should be forbidden to try.<br>
<br>
Like I've said, I'd like us to just see how this first round goes.  It's too early for new alliances/guilds to be pushing to get on it anyways.  We don't even know how well it will all work out yet, so I just ask that we do at least a few kills before we set rules in stone.  Remember most other rotation mobs are not random, so Sev might be a bit more complex than any other mobs on rotation.<br>
<br>
For now...good luck FR!<br>
